Johnson's baby powder has traditionally been used on babies around their genitals to keep them dry (and help prevent nappy rash)...and also because it smells nice. I gather from this, that some women have bought into the idea that if it works for babies, then it must work for them. Advertising and the media have been promoting the idea that women's vaginas are not nice unless they are smelling of sweetness/perfume, (clearly so that they will buy their products), so many women believe this and use the product in the mistaken belief that they need it. A woman's vagina is a delicate balance of natural secretions and bacteria. If anything chemical or 'unnatural' enters the vagina, then it can cause imbalances of these secretions and bacteria. There is no need for anything to be used except water and un-perfumed soap to keep it clean. Here endeth the lesson!



